<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-4DD678AF-BE6F-460E-B97A-CE312D1E6245" version="1" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-4DD678AF-BE6F-460E-B97A-CE312D1E6245" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">19 The function of the External Output</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-34C6A3E5-E809-4139-80CC-275A8CCF9EDC"><p class="- topic/p ">How does external output function (also called winder). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The winder has the following function: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul " id="UL_1E8AAE01B886471B95C2FD581F087E96"><li class="- topic/li " id="LI_46C11F9DF4D54302AE10345A44E2190A"><p class="- topic/p ">Take up the printed media and wind it on a core. 
</p></li></ul><fig class="- topic/fig " id="FIG_0DCDAD60E8B24951BE1E626B82578BBE"><title class="- topic/title ">External output</title><image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-2F6B9E4F-0EAC-48D9-BA39-86D8D8BC0274-low.png" id="IMAGE_C842573C775E419195126866FA8BB766" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-2F6B9E4F-0EAC-48D9-BA39-86D8D8BC0274-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">The leading edge of the media is taped by the operator on a core. At the end of a job the core withe the printed media can be handled with a lift mechanism. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="GUID-F5034822-753A-4C8B-A7CD-E44CE7EBD702" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Overview</title><p class="- topic/p ">The external output has the following sub-functions: 
</p><ul id="UL_C81BDCE236F046D2908D26959FE12B08" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_753A80F99FF743BBB7B388095D75B6E1" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Interface 
</p></li><li id="LI_FD162A35A3C84815A66C70041B964DA2" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Guide plate 
</p></li><li id="LI_373AFB06FF464D77B1932A1BE2F3E45E" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Blouse forming device and blouse control 
</p></li><li id="LI_0F0B1D2FD10F4C9D9577B2AB3A38FD95" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Clamp 
</p></li><li id="LI_E982110124E34AB9A6C0DF2F5B8C8F51" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Flanges 
</p></li><li id="LI_47DF4A747D8A4636AF3A23558756256D" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Guide tube 
</p></li><li id="LI_4AA4A4C302514C778D958E97E5E6E07C" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Manual cut 
</p></li><li id="LI_6DC7F0B871914173A60C71C6D3BFA94C" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Drive of the core 
</p></li></ul><fig id="FIG_CB88325E54824CEB8D73922BA68C268B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-16891B5E-3C60-43E7-AE99-53D53D291C5F-low.png" id="IMAGE_61C79B2B87FF42DAB8E6BACEF3655140" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-16891B5E-3C60-43E7-AE99-53D53D291C5F-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="SECTION_699C6367B0664A62B7E22E588560C9F7" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Basic sequence</title><table id="TABLE_2EED1D90E9F24429B6B9D2663296CB4D" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Initial situation: 
</p><ul id="UL_837EBB1AE8A14F81874EBF8620DD2F73" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_BA2AFF22F34541D08AA10756C48C78BE" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The guide plate closes the gap between the output unit and the guide tube before the leading edge is fed out. 
</p></li></ul></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_8602CD772880401C92BAD1433FC04C12" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A8BF2141-B2BD-432B-9093-79F874DC03E3-low.png" id="IMAGE_0964A91B87924D88822BC1C8B5E5C141" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A8BF2141-B2BD-432B-9093-79F874DC03E3-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ul id="UL_EA924B74DD2B49AA82407FD04BF02D82" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_23FCA588C5E34DD1A12E5A3F6D8E75E1" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The media passes the guide tube and the guide plate is lowered. 
</p></li></ul></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_962F9BE5F0E142CBAA2B64099B3DC576" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-9F7C9471-AC07-409C-8A86-115C8A571D7B-low.png" id="IMAGE_D18EF81B5AB44043AAE273D2583E33D4" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-9F7C9471-AC07-409C-8A86-115C8A571D7B-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ul id="UL_CC1DEB00891A4909B7069D7F0CDB6656" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_D511B64919F544418B0C3B3B87172754" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The leading edge of the media is near the tape position (close to the core). 
</p></li><li id="LI_9E3E0BE326DD4137855B07095FA7B149" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> The clamp is lowered to hold the media on th guide tube. 
</p></li><li id="LI_580688080D9843D78E3BD3C407866426" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The media can be taped on the core. 
</p></li></ul></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_84EF789D0A394720B842E6121E4E9252" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-DB2CAC97-1899-4085-A187-23A1F0863F4D-low.png" id="IMAGE_7C599263B5664D879A760CF1C87C7B5B" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-DB2CAC97-1899-4085-A187-23A1F0863F4D-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Initial blouse forming: 
</p><ul id="UL_FAEA9436713B4E00A3662DF525C14185" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_69E110AFFBA4404B992B74CFF124ADDC" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The guide plate is lowered completely 
</p></li><li id="LI_285796EB2C5043D38DF154C477779892" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The blouse forming device pushes the media downwards. 
</p></li></ul></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_17A8D5326A3A454A92E1597C53C1063D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-EE4151B4-8A5B-4F03-9D71-7EF3679BBEA9-low.png" id="IMAGE_7FF0607207874E9F94C3968D6E316800" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-EE4151B4-8A5B-4F03-9D71-7EF3679BBEA9-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Blouse formed: 
</p><ul id="UL_065A10AE0B6042BD87485C863DD79EC8" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_5AB313DEDA1F4CF1ACA267678D80D2B4" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The blouse is formed as the blouse forming device is in the lowest position. 
</p></li></ul></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_F294C2D5283648FA8ECD5F10034D382E" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-C954FBD2-30B9-4DAE-BB1A-0BC70F37BC57-low.png" id="IMAGE_F6938203BF82445AB64D7C43A3AA98CE" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C954FBD2-30B9-4DAE-BB1A-0BC70F37BC57-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Release the clamp and start winding: 
</p><ul id="UL_E6DA7C1FC6614594A844B9B283A4BB9E" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_21A058BABA1F46349B5998EA634D03F7" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The operator has indicated that the media is taped on the core and positioned the flanges. 
</p></li><li id="LI_19AFEA62770144D4AAE2C127A8AF9813" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The clamp is now released. 
</p></li><li id="LI_3D26500A10B74B68B02699B5DF0BCE45" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">At the moment the lowest blouse sensor is activated the winding of the media on the core is started. 
</p></li></ul></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_9E908EE000BB432D940B7065A3DA8734" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-888ACF29-C62B-495E-ABDA-2BFC984EE85F-low.png" id="IMAGE_0DC3ABC411DE4F1982C0B68C98EEA478" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-888ACF29-C62B-495E-ABDA-2BFC984EE85F-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="SECTION_1FC7DA0808174C1C94CC8A660EE48A8F" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Loose winding</title><table id="TABLE_83D83D0946F84BB3959F6F7EDA0C5EFF" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Media passes the guide tube. Clamp is open. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_C6007E537520409C9257745E7FBFCD77" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A5E997AA-66D3-4A47-80BE-91B48D2E7EE3-low.png" id="IMAGE_6C82003D671D41B5A4A88BD82BE4A7C8" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A5E997AA-66D3-4A47-80BE-91B48D2E7EE3-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The leading edge of the media is at the tape position. The clamp is closed. WOO ? starts. Key operator is requested to tape. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_E54CAA1DFDCC40A1BAA73B1F67BDC776" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-73D7DCF3-FF38-4C6A-A69A-68F8A45F8A9B-low.png" id="IMAGE_B544D2072BEA4C688BA7215E701507F5" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-73D7DCF3-FF38-4C6A-A69A-68F8A45F8A9B-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The guide plate goes down. Blouse forming device gets in contact with the media. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_E3B660ECBD894C9A886C7B5C018398AF" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-BF960FED-4C20-4507-B3D2-F8F64EBA2AF5-low.png" id="IMAGE_55D5418A30824E4BAC886C3077BB9209" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-BF960FED-4C20-4507-B3D2-F8F64EBA2AF5-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Blouse is forming as printing continues. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_97682374A09C407A859A8B2DCA24809E" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-C89E749E-C0FD-4025-9735-15DDB405BF19-low.png" id="IMAGE_901B0292BE314D07B2BB63517ED13D58" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C89E749E-C0FD-4025-9735-15DDB405BF19-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Leading edge taped on core. Flanges positioned by the key operator. The blouse is fully formed. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_54AD49D97E8F4A36AA24FC077CA10EEC" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-73FE31AD-0831-4602-8498-623878FE16D2-low.png" id="IMAGE_DB9B3550E423492FB9E8EE1B82392427" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-73FE31AD-0831-4602-8498-623878FE16D2-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">After confirmation by the operator. Clamp is open and winding can start when blouse has the right level. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_2828B664047D48DD80CA20CB7E4486A4" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-08C4AFC8-46B0-4BC9-97B1-5F1566E15D34-low.png" id="IMAGE_4B4E058C9A304ACC82024402E34E47F1" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-08C4AFC8-46B0-4BC9-97B1-5F1566E15D34-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="SECTION_FB9ECBBBAEC74178956878FB8380F481" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Cut and loose winding</title><table id="TABLE_6EA89EABE6BE421095BF216372B49C59" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Ready to cut. Blouse is getting shorter and shorter. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_A26EEE3C636B4CB4AB0F451A3CFA87C5" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-E668A858-6125-42C7-BD4F-B7FA5019BCC5-low.png" id="IMAGE_2244BA09671A4E758A5D944E21972616" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E668A858-6125-42C7-BD4F-B7FA5019BCC5-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Blouse removed. Guide plate and clamp can close. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_328080C5466840E1971D2BAA42240C95" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-E5F9681B-CF7A-421E-8757-BA8E39E46203-low.png" id="IMAGE_F952DADE8F9F4EA2B9470768924DD393" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E5F9681B-CF7A-421E-8757-BA8E39E46203-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Guide plate up and clamp closed. Media is cut. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_E1673AA59A73422796F72122628B222A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-04245260-1781-4457-BEEE-E9689B402C1A-low.png" id="IMAGE_D4641A0A84CC4D939CC55F2F0A04542A" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-04245260-1781-4457-BEEE-E9689B402C1A-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Clamp partially open. Trailing edge removed. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_3D9B1AD918FB4F4F8E17EE326D5350A5" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-5729A1BF-2444-4D81-94CE-8D20E5A5FA01-low.png" id="IMAGE_466ED2645EDC4E2B85C971718BCD759F" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-5729A1BF-2444-4D81-94CE-8D20E5A5FA01-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="SECTION_82CC9CAB7B474551B3D50C2598500D0D" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Tight winding</title><table id="TABLE_F86256C0494D496EAA6FB65E865D5A26" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Media transported to tap position. Key operator requested to tape the media. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_72B29CB8FEEB475C81965EFE63C4A911" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-57B056B6-BAE7-46C6-B367-B929626BEB77-low.png" id="IMAGE_E366C46B3ECA4B41892C7E51C0120FDB" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-57B056B6-BAE7-46C6-B367-B929626BEB77-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Key operator has taped and acknowledge. Guide plate opened. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_7DE19479BCE14394A8DD4DA70E00C38C" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-39226937-A8DE-486D-940D-10BE0004F931-low.png" id="IMAGE_59FD91F9371C493B8612B037D66EDF8C" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-39226937-A8DE-486D-940D-10BE0004F931-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Request to move the tension bar and place the tension bar. After acknowledge the printing starts. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_093A34196E6142D9B2C80A24C5068A1E" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-82EE585E-1656-4296-BF11-FEAEDA5931CE-low.png" id="IMAGE_4340BA6B857142A995B75DF53C7C3692" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-82EE585E-1656-4296-BF11-FEAEDA5931CE-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Printing has started. Blouse is forced by tension bar. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_F7A0BB00333947769A40A307F0AA672D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D8810274-DC17-488D-BF0B-7395D1484C56-low.png" id="IMAGE_9A916907AE014E44B55E84F2DB569667" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D8810274-DC17-488D-BF0B-7395D1484C56-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Blouse at lowest level. Winding starts. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_E9D2CE721C6E47C4ABF8F8375FCF631A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-AB857DFB-187D-4835-B22D-FBB55A56502C-low.png" id="IMAGE_F58ECBE87F5945A7B19339E2B8AFF1E4" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-AB857DFB-187D-4835-B22D-FBB55A56502C-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="SECTION_94D1B0054ADA414A9C24FCF1B12843D0" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Cut and tight winding</title><table id="TABLE_83CB39BCF6DC4236B1161C70E22F3730" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Ready to cut. Blouse is getting shorter and shorter. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_3289DD05F04A4B1C81CC407F6F66833B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-E224CBB7-D91F-4D46-940A-6D85C5F78AF3-low.png" id="IMAGE_CB86B7892605402BAC8C4DDA11E8144B" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E224CBB7-D91F-4D46-940A-6D85C5F78AF3-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Blouse is gone. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The key operator is requested to remove the tension bar. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_7FEB58AF3B8A4C859D538C9042C4B69D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-151E6DA1-78B8-4E88-B93D-E29949C95FB3-low.png" id="IMAGE_F91C03BBC4F648318EB40EF04D14454A" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-151E6DA1-78B8-4E88-B93D-E29949C95FB3-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Guide plate and clamp closes. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Cut of the media takes place. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The trailing edge is removed by the take up roll. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_28C36401E5DC40F7ADFB17F5D219E808" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-82EE585E-1656-4296-BF11-FEAEDA5931CE-low.png" id="IMAGE_88E67A35AD1543769099A7651CD2FF80" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-82EE585E-1656-4296-BF11-FEAEDA5931CE-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="SECTION_9B626780723F43D098BFA436BC9DEDF7" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">No winding and cut</title><table id="TABLE_F1E400BB5A9A4BD8B5421078B632508A" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The printed media is passing the winder. The key operator is responsible for the guidance of the media. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_7B237310268842C18F76DB6BA471E5BF" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-6FA689EC-5BFD-47EB-ABE3-176670A8C4BE-low.png" id="IMAGE_59870D9CD65D4BB1BC4F05A0B20200E5" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6FA689EC-5BFD-47EB-ABE3-176670A8C4BE-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The key operator is indicating that he would like to cut the media. The clamp is closed. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_CEACDB00F4BD44DE9E14E88547AEF71E" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-0BEA3CE9-E474-4F8F-AC1A-023E9FE0B046-low.png" id="IMAGE_10210CB09ABE4583820B566DB112C22E" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0BEA3CE9-E474-4F8F-AC1A-023E9FE0B046-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Depending on the media an auto cut or manual cut takes place. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The key operator handles the trailing edge of the media and indicated that the media is removed. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_7E079CF64A404A78AA86B65CEA8DF2AC" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-0ED68D5C-9182-4903-B9EF-4A4A8AD5767C-low.png" id="IMAGE_0694D39618784CFDB70F82EFDDF1E324" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0ED68D5C-9182-4903-B9EF-4A4A8AD5767C-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-3225DD38-160F-42B4-A279-10AA00359615" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Interface</title><p class="- topic/p "> The media is fed from the print surface (A) to the knife unit (B) and over the level interface to the external output. The media steps down in each step towards the external output unit. 
</p><fig id="FIG_20F614660E964975BC71910EFEDEF002" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-8FB1E7ED-09AA-415B-A37C-201D7C219A92-low.png" id="IMAGE_8184A88662684906A349E3FE272A3DFC" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-8FB1E7ED-09AA-415B-A37C-201D7C219A92-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-1070FD93-CFAD-4011-8EAB-1BB9341AD686" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Guide plate</title><p class="- topic/p "> The guide plate (A) guides in the upper position the media towards the core of the winder. Aim is to feed the media without wrinkles to the core. 
</p><fig id="FIG_FEDBE5B04B6647BAB84FE427B045DB81" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-3A326817-F7FF-472E-A562-B798721F5ADC-low.png" id="IMAGE_A770DA820E8B4013A042129BCC4B7924" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-3A326817-F7FF-472E-A562-B798721F5ADC-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> A melinex guide flap (A) in taped on the backside of the guide flap. The flap is used to bridge the the gap between the guide plate and the guide tube. 
</p><fig id="FIG_E76B36B46E474636B2BC4FAF210BB314" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A8EDC636-9B37-49B2-8995-001985D1D804-low.png" id="IMAGE_2001D39E16BC420DB30566296D2DF594" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A8EDC636-9B37-49B2-8995-001985D1D804-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-17AD9DE0-68AE-4EE1-89FF-539760AEAF25" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Blouse forming device and blouse control </title><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">External output winder blouse high sensor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 19B2 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">EXO_WND_BLOUSE_HIGH_SE</compsignal></comp> <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">External output winder blouse low sensor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 19B6 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">EXO_WND_BLOUSE_LOW_SE1</compsignal></comp>
</p><p class="- topic/p ">2 Optical sensors ( <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">External output winder blouse high sensor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 19B2 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">EXO_WND_BLOUSE_HIGH_SE</compsignal></comp> (A) and <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">External output winder blouse low sensor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 19B6 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">EXO_WND_BLOUSE_LOW_SE1</compsignal></comp> (B) are used to detect the position of the blouse of the media. 
</p><fig id="FIG_6D29D979E3E2460BA8E260A468A8B36A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-76716912-3A23-4B7A-B2D1-A0EB4EF25200-low.png" id="IMAGE_BA90810C69894AA0B0E796315DE25AC8" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-76716912-3A23-4B7A-B2D1-A0EB4EF25200-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">At the moment the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">External output winder blouse low sensor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 19B6 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">EXO_WND_BLOUSE_LOW_SE1</compsignal></comp> sensor (B) is activated the motor <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">External output winder drive motor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 19M1 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">EXO_WND_DRV_MO</compsignal></comp> is activated. The media is rolled up on the core. As soon as the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">External output winder blouse high sensor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 19B2 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">EXO_WND_BLOUSE_HIGH_SE</compsignal></comp> sensor (A) is de-activated the motor is stopped. 
</p></section><section id="SECTION_9F3831A3F51848BB929F150292FF4CA0" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Clamp</title><fig id="FIG_5E9E0607CFD74C51A5E311B5ECDA2BD8" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-5C8A4EB3-1953-42C8-AE3D-86716AF69597-low.png" id="IMAGE_521C1A09600C49919F0E6FD75BB43031" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-5C8A4EB3-1953-42C8-AE3D-86716AF69597-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">The drive motor rotates the pulley on which an eccentric (A) is mounted. The pulley is mounted on a shaft. The shaft is beared in the frame on the left and right hand side. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">(B) pivot points 
</p></section><section id="SECTION_A9F745E19D62469F962B74E11F1A4B59" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Flanges</title><p class="- topic/p "><?xm-replace_text Paragraph?>
</p></section><section id="SECTION_85B00A59A18B410998E8D7BDD3AD925C" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Manual cut</title><fig id="FIG_C0B58E957A4A45C5BA2C9D4574C771AA" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A518727D-24E3-4897-ACFE-3094A2FD2115-low.png" id="IMAGE_B453A45F94B94AC4AFD9AA4C89AEC34D" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A518727D-24E3-4897-ACFE-3094A2FD2115-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Some media are not cut by the printer. A manual cut of the media by the operator is required. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">At the lower side of the guidance the manual cut strip is attached. The operator can place a knife between the strip and the profile. 
</p></section><section id="SECTION_1CA05FE3B1AA462781BCB5139DCA4B2C" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Drive of the core</title><fig id="FIG_3983A468B1084249B9F07010B42412DB" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-0C8BC853-0730-41DC-95EB-BB9410DA25F4-low.png" id="IMAGE_69E5865555AB497C98974AE03737754F" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0C8BC853-0730-41DC-95EB-BB9410DA25F4-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">The core used in the external output is the same core as used in the media drawer. Motor <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">External output winder drive motor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 19M1 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">EXO_WND_DRV_MO</compsignal></comp> drives the gear (A). Via a drive belt the pulley (B) is activated. Gear (C) activates the gear (D) of the core of the external output. 
</p></section></conbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-77E3E148-DF16-4838-9432-CE905B393B0C.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Functional description</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</concept>